<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="flowering">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Flowering.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">May to July (September).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
Wet, somewhat nitrified meadows, stony places, swampy areas and psychro-xerophilic pastures (
<normalizedToken originalValue="“cervunales”">&quot;cervunales&quot;</normalizedToken>
), on granites or slates; 1560-2400 m a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
Endemic to the CN of the Iberian Peninsula. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Spa.</emphasis>
: Av Cc Le Lu O Or (S) Sa (Za). For a representative list of studied materials, see Suppl. material 1.
</paragraph>
